subject: p14236258
Findings: When compared to prior, there has been no significant interval change. Lungs are grossly clear. There is no large effusion or edema. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is within normal limits. Rightward deviation of the trachea at the thoracic inlet is compatible with known underlying left-sided thyroid enlargement. Surgical clips seen projecting over the thoracic inlet. Left chest wall dual lumen central venous catheter is now seen. Multiple vascular stents project over the left upper extremity and mediastinum. Severe degenerative changes noted at the shoulders bilaterally. Old healed right posterior rib fractures are also noted.
